SIMPLE: refuse
RECORDS: 5

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Refuse
<hw>Re*fuse"</hw> <pr>(r?*f?z")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Refused</conjf>
<pr>(-f?zd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Refusing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>refuser</ets>, either
from (assumed) LL. <ets>refusare</ets> to refuse, v. freq. of L.
<ets>refundere</ets> to pour back, give back, restore (see
<er>Refund</er> to repay), or. fr. L. <ets>recusare</ets> to decline,
refuse cf. <er>Accuse</er>, <er>Ruse</er>), influenced by L.
<ets>refutare</ets> to drive back, repel, refute. Cf.
<er>Refute</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To deny, as a request, demand,
invitation, or command; to decline to do or grant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That never yet <qex>refused</qex> your hest.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>To throw back, or cause to keep
back (as the center, a wing, or a flank), out of the regular aligment
when troops ar<?/ about to engage the enemy; <as>as, to <ex>refuse</ex>
the right wing while the left wing attacks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To decline to accept; to reject; to deny the request
or petition of; <as>as, to <ex>refuse</ex> a suitor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cunning workman never doth <qex>refuse</qex>⟦br⟧
The meanest tool that he may chance to use.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To disown.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Refuse</xex> thy name.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Refuse
<hw>Re*fuse"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To deny compliance; not to
comply.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Too proud to ask, too humble to <qex>refuse</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Garth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If ye <qex>refuse</qex> . . . ye shall be devoured with the
sword.</q> <rj><qau>Isa. i. 20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Refuse
<hw>Re*fuse"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Refusal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Fairfax.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Refuse
<hw>Ref`use</hw> <pr>(r?f"?s;277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>refus</ets> refusal, also, that which is refused. See
<er>Refuse</er> to deny.]</ety> <def>That which is refused or rejected
as useless; waste or worthless matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Dregs; sediment; scum; recrement;
dross.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refuse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Refuse
<hw>Ref"use</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Refused; rejected; hence; left as
unworthy of acceptance; of no value; worthless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Everything that was vile and <qex>refuse</qex>, that they
destroyed utterly.</q> <rj><qau>1. Sam. xv. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refuser</ent>⟦br⟧
